            <section class="project-summary">
                <span class="image fit">
                    <img src="images/attrition dashboard.png" alt="HR Dashboard Screenshot" />
                </span>
                <h2>üìå Objective</h2>
                <p>To build an interactive dashboard that visualizes employee attrition trends based on key metrics such as age, department, education level, and job satisfaction. The goal was to assist HR teams in identifying patterns contributing to turnover and develop retention strategies.</p>

                <h2>üìä Key Findings</h2>
                <ul>
                    <li>Attrition rates were highest among employees under age 30 and over age 50.</li>
                    <li>Job satisfaction below average correlated strongly with voluntary exits.</li>
                    <li>The Sales and Research departments had the highest attrition rates.</li>
                    <li>Employees with fewer years at the company were more likely to leave.</li>
                </ul>

                <h2>üõ† Tools & Techniques</h2>
                <ul>
                    <li><strong>Tableau:</strong> Dashboard design, interactivity (filters by department/age/satisfaction)</li>
                    <li><strong>Excel:</strong> Preprocessing and data cleaning</li>
                </ul>

                <h2>üîó Resources</h2>
                <ul>
                    <li><a href="https://www.kaggle.com/datasets/pavansubhasht/ibm-hr-analytics-attrition-dataset" target="_blank">Dataset on Kaggle</a></li>
                    <li><a href="https://github.com/CraigJustin92/hr-employee-attrition" target="_blank">GitHub Repo</a></li>
                    <li><a href="https://public.tableau.com/views/HRAnalytics_17532324058090/HRATTRITIONANALYTICS" target="_blank">View Dashboard on Tableau Public</a></li>
                </ul>

                <h2>üìÅ Scope Summary</h2>
                <ul>
                    <li>Project Duration: ~1 week</li>
                    <li>Role: Sole Contributor (Data Analyst & Visualization Designer)</li>
                    <li>Focus: Exploratory data analysis (EDA), HR insight delivery, visual storytelling</li>
                </ul>

